race.description: Annabelle Cleeland Mp Member For Euroa Handicap
race.comment: LES BRAVES (15) has been in the money in his last couple of runs, and has started favourite in all 4 starts this prep, most recently finishing second at Cranbourne just over a fortnight ago. Stick with him, and follow your money. LARIO (8) resumes after five months off, and he will be a lot stronger this season. He was a minor placegetter when fresh last prep over 1400m at Echuca, and with 3 jumpouts under his belt, he is set to give this a big shake. ASAWIN (4) returned from a break with a tough win by a neck over 1350m at Donald nearly 4 weeks ago. He won't find this much harder, and he is a big each-way chance again. FACTCHECK (9) has changed stables after a good 3-year-old campaign last season. Watch the markets.
